						<div class="postbody">Banks can be loaded into multiple slots, so something that's visible at $A000-$BFFF can also be loaded at $C000-$FFFF.<br /><br />As for the DPCM vs. PCM thing, I always thought that DPCM was what we called the 1-bit per sample audio format that the NES is able to play automatically, while PCM were the 7-bit samples you can manually write to the APU.</div>

