						<div class="postbody">Thank you for all that information guys!<br /><br />Just a quick response regarding the cheering sample. I have this 'dpcm' working within my mmc5 rom, and having it being read within my $A000-$BFFF bank, I have the cheer coexisting with my sound engine AND an irq split screen at the same time. So I guess the comment earlier, about writes to $4010 is the trick to load samples in other address ranges rather than $C000-$FFFF.<br /><br />Again thanks for the clarifications on dpcm, so now I know its only 1 of 'em.<br /><br />Btw, to those curious on the mmc5 pcm, the cheering sample worked on the mmc5's pcm, when I changed the $4010 to $5010, (I think that's the mmc5 register, thinking off the top of my head atm)</div>

